<definition-item date-revised="2023-08-01"><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">F03H1/00</classification-symbol><definition-title>Using plasma to produce a reactive propulsive thrust  (generating plasma <class-ref scheme="cpc">H05H1/00</class-ref> ){(ion sources per se <class-ref scheme="cpc">H01J27/02</class-ref>, ion sources for plasma processing or ion beams <class-ref scheme="cpc">H01J37/08</class-ref>)}</definition-title><definition-statement>
      <section-title>Definition statement</section-title>
      <section-body><paragraph-text type="preamble">This place covers:</paragraph-text><paragraph-text type="body">Engines exhausting ions or a plasma (ions and electrons) to produce a reactive propulsive thrust.</paragraph-text><paragraph-text type="body">Details thereof.</paragraph-text></section-body>
    </definition-statement><relationship>
      <section-title>Relationships with other classification places</section-title>
      <section-body><paragraph-text type="body">Multi-purpose ion sources which can be used inter alia as ion thruster should be classified only in <class-ref scheme="cpc">H01J27/00</class-ref> and lower.</paragraph-text></section-body>
